    <text id="B0230T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Crawford writes Jackson in reference to a lot in Waynesboro and the claim of a
                    Mr. Morrison to it.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Freedmans Bureau<lb/>Mr. Jackson at Staunton
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-07-22">July 22nd <abbr expan="1867">/67</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mr. Jackson</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I talked to Mr. Morrison <add hand="h1" place="inline">and wife</add> this
                    morning <add hand="h1" place="inline">he said</add> that if they had an doubt he
                    could show anyone that he could give a good right to the lot, and if they are
                    not <orig reg="certified">certefied</orig> they can take the building off when
                    they get ready.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours <orig reg="etc">&amp;c</orig></salute>
                    <signed>John L. A. Crawford<lb/>Trustee</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. Baldwin is not to blame, he was overpowered by the
                        balance of the Committee. It is out of his power at this time for him to
                        come to see you but as soon as he can he will come.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
